:class:`~icalendar.prop.binary.vBinary` now stores the raw ``bytes`` of the value internally, so non-UTF-8 binary data round-trips losslessly (previously it was decoded as text and corrupted). As a consequence, :attr:`vBinary.ical_value` now returns the raw stored bytes instead of base64-decoding them, and no longer raises :class:`ValueError` for non-base64 input. ``ical_value`` was introduced in 7.1.0, so the external impact is limited. @uwezkhan
